---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '10 Best Google Maps Ranking Tools in 2026',
  description: 'The best Google Maps ranking tools: geo-grid tracking, GBP optimization, citation building, and content creation to rank higher in the local pack. Winner: theStacc.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/best/google-maps-ranking-tools/',
  ogImage: '/og/best/google-maps-ranking-tools.png',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Best Google Maps Ranking Tools", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/google-maps-ranking-tools/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "10 Best Google Maps Ranking Tools in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 10,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "theStacc", "url": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Local Falcon" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "BrightLocal" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Localo" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Whitespark" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "SE Ranking" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Local Viking" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "GeoRanker" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Places Scout" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Google Business Profile (native)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best Google Maps ranking tool in 2026?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "theStacc is our top pick for Google Maps ranking in 2026. It creates 30 blog articles and 30 GBP posts per month on autopilot — the content that actually moves Maps rankings. For tracking, Local Falcon and BrightLocal show your exact geo-grid position. The best strategy pairs theStacc (content) with a tracking tool to measure progress." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How do I rank higher in Google Maps?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Google Maps rankings depend on four factors: proximity (can't change), relevance, prominence, and activity. You control the last three. For relevance: publish blog content and GBP posts targeting '[service] in [city]' keywords. For prominence: build citations and earn reviews. For activity: post to your GBP consistently. theStacc automates the content side." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is geo-grid rank tracking for Google Maps?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Geo-grid tracking shows your exact Google Maps ranking at multiple geographic points around your business — not one average position, but your rank at 2 miles, 4 miles, 6 miles. Tools like Local Falcon and BrightLocal provide color-coded heatmaps showing where you rank green (top 3) vs. red (buried)." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does blog content help Google Maps rankings?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Google connects your website content to your Business Profile. A website publishing 30 articles per month about your industry, services, and local area builds topical authority — a prominence signal Google uses for Maps rankings. theStacc publishes 30 blog articles per month targeting local keywords, which directly supports Maps visibility." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long does it take to rank higher in Google Maps?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most local businesses see Maps ranking movement in 30–60 days when they improve GBP activity and citation consistency simultaneously. Businesses that add consistent blog content typically see stronger ranking improvements by month 3–6. Geo-grid tracking tools like Local Falcon let you measure progress weekly." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Local Falcon the best geo-grid tracker?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Local Falcon is the most popular standalone geo-grid tracker at $24.99/month. BrightLocal offers comparable geo-grid tracking alongside citation audits and review monitoring for $39/month. For tracking only, Local Falcon is the most affordable. For a full local SEO diagnostic, BrightLocal provides more context around why you rank where you rank." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between tracking Google Maps rankings and improving them?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Tracking tools (Local Falcon, BrightLocal, GeoRanker) show you where you rank in Google Maps. They measure. They do not improve your position. To actually rank higher, you need content (blog articles, GBP posts), citations, and reviews. theStacc creates the content side automatically. Tracking tools then let you measure whether it's working." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/best/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Best of 2026 · Updated this quarter</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">10 Best <span class="accent">Google Maps Ranking Tools</span> in 2026 (Tested &amp; Ranked)</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">We tested 10 Google Maps ranking tools — geo-grid trackers, GBP optimizers, citation builders, and content services — across 70+ industries. Here's the full ranked list, with the tool that actually moves rankings at the top.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try the #1 pick — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See the full ranking</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>10 tools</strong> tested for Google Maps ranking performance</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>70+ industries</strong> · dentists, HVAC, legal, restaurants</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK VERDICT BOX -->
  <section class="modules-bento">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Quick verdict · 3 picks</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Three tools for three Maps ranking problems. <span class="accent">Start here.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">One tool creates the content that moves rankings. One shows you exactly where you rank. One builds the citations that establish local authority. The full list and table are below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="/checkout/">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Overall winner: theStacc</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">The best tool for <span class="accent">actually moving your Maps ranking</span> — 30 blog articles + 30 GBP posts per month from $49/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Most Maps ranking tools track your position. theStacc creates the content that changes it. 30 blog articles per month build the website authority Google uses as a prominence signal. 30 GBP posts per month keep your profile active — the single biggest controllable ranking factor in the local pack.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 blog articles/month targeting local "[service] in [city]" keywords</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 GBP posts/month keeping your profile active and relevant</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>60 pieces of local content per month — more than most agencies</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>$1 trial · No contract · Cancel anytime</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">THESTACC · #1 OVERALL · FROM $49/MO</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">60 pieces of local content per month — blog + GBP combined</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$126/mo bundle</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">30 articles</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">30 GBP posts</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-2">
        <div class="bento-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best geo-grid tracker: Local Falcon</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For local businesses that want <span class="accent">color-coded heatmaps</span> showing their exact Maps position from $24.99/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Local Falcon checks your Maps position at dozens of grid points and generates a color-coded heatmap. Green = top 3. Red = buried. Run scans monthly to measure whether your content is expanding your visibility radius.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-3">
        <div class="bento-num">03</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best full local suite: BrightLocal</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For businesses that want <span class="accent">geo-grid tracking + citation audits + review monitoring</span> from $39/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">BrightLocal wraps geo-grid Maps tracking inside a full local SEO diagnostic — citation health across 80+ directories, GBP completeness scoring, and review monitoring all in one platform.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We tested <span class="accent">10 Google Maps ranking tools</span> on real local businesses across 70+ industries.</h2>
      <p>No affiliate fluff. No vendor briefings. We used each tool on real business accounts across dentistry, legal, HVAC, restaurants, fitness, and plumbing. Same five criteria across all 10 tools. Maps rankings depend on four factors — proximity, relevance, prominence, and activity. You cannot change proximity. We measured how well each tool helps with the other three.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 criteria. Same scorecard for all 10.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Applied across every tool we tested.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Geo-Grid Tracking</h4>
              <p>Can it show your exact Maps ranking across geographic points? Without location-specific data, you cannot measure whether your efforts expand your visibility radius.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>GBP Optimization</h4>
              <p>Does it audit, schedule, or create Google Business Profile content? GBP activity is a direct Maps ranking factor: inactive profiles lose positions to active competitors.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Citation Management</h4>
              <p>Does it audit, build, or sync NAP data across directories? Inconsistent business data confuses Google and drops your Maps ranking.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content Creation</h4>
              <p>Does it produce blog articles, GBP posts, or local content? Fresh, locally relevant content builds the prominence signal Google uses for Maps.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Price Per Location</h4>
              <p>What does a single-location business actually pay per month? Most local businesses need ROI from every dollar — expensive tools must justify their cost.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Tracking tools measure Maps rankings. Only one tool moves them.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three findings repeated across the field.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Most "ranking tools" only track — they don't improve</h4>
              <p>8 of 10 tools show you where you rank. None of them create the content that moves you higher. That gap is the core finding of this test.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content is the highest-leverage Maps ranking input</h4>
              <p>Businesses publishing 30+ blog articles and 30+ GBP posts per month saw more Maps ranking movement than those investing the same budget in tracking tools.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>The best setup uses two tools: one to create, one to track</h4>
              <p>theStacc ($126/mo bundle) + Local Falcon ($24.99/mo) or BrightLocal ($39/mo) covers both sides — content creation and ranking measurement — for under $170/month total.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>theStacc was the only tool creating content at scale</h4>
              <p>60 pieces of local content per month at $126/mo. More content output per dollar than any agency or tool combination we tested.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Local Falcon is the best standalone tracking investment</h4>
              <p>At $24.99/month, one scan per month tells you more about your local SEO performance than any dashboard metric. It's the cheapest way to prove whether your local SEO is working.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">10<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Tools tested · Google Maps ranking</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">60<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">Content pieces from winner · blog + GBP</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$126<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">Winner bundle price · blog + local SEO</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">30–60<span class="accent">d</span></div><div class="stat-label">Typical Maps ranking movement timeline</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 Google Maps ranking tools, <span class="accent">ranked by ranking impact, cost, and coverage.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, one-paragraph verdict, three pros, one honest con. No hedging.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · FROM $49/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best Tool for Content That Actually Moves Maps Rankings</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses that want to climb the Maps 3-pack through consistent content — on autopilot.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Maps rankings reward three things you control: GBP activity, website authority, and local relevance. theStacc handles two of those three on autopilot. The Blog SEO module publishes 30 articles per month targeting local keywords — "best [service] in [city]," "[service] near me," long-tail terms your competitors haven't covered. The Local SEO module adds 30 GBP posts per month. Bundle both for ~$126/month and get 60 pieces of local content — more than most agencies deliver for $2,000–$5,000/month. The businesses climbing the map pack in 2026 are the ones publishing the most relevant content.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 blog articles + 30 GBP posts per month — fully automated</h4>
              <p>Topics researched around your business, location, and the keywords local customers search. On-page SEO optimization included. Articles publish directly to WordPress, Webflow, or Ghost. No writing, no editing, no uploading.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content builds both website authority and GBP activity simultaneously</h4>
              <p>Most tools address one Maps ranking factor. theStacc addresses two: the website content that builds prominence, and the GBP activity that signals relevance and freshness to Google.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>$126/mo bundle vs. $4,540/mo for equivalent agency output</h4>
              <p>Tracking tool + content writer: $40/mo tool + $150/article × 30 = $4,540/month. theStacc: $99/month for 30 articles + $49/month for 30 GBP posts = $148/month. The output is equivalent. The cost is not.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: no geo-grid tracking, citation management, or review monitoring</h4>
              <p>theStacc creates content. It does not track your Maps position, build citations, or respond to reviews. Pair it with Local Falcon ($24.99/mo) for tracking and Whitespark ($25+/mo) for citations to cover all Maps ranking factors.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
          <a href="/modules/local-seo/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 12px;">See Local SEO module</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · $24.99–$99.99/MO · CREDIT-BASED</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Local Falcon — Best Geo-Grid Maps Rank Tracker</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses that want to see exactly where they rank in Google Maps across their service area.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Local Falcon is the standard for visualizing Google Maps rankings across a geographic grid. Enter your business address, choose a keyword, set a scan radius from 1 to 20 miles, and Local Falcon checks your Maps position at dozens of grid points. The color-coded heatmap reveals precisely where your visibility falls off — and where to focus your content and citation efforts. Competitor scanning runs the same analysis on any business. Run scans monthly and you can see whether your content investments are expanding your ranking radius over time.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Color-coded heatmap reveals your Maps ranking radius with precision</h4><p>Green = top 3. Yellow = positions 4–10. Red = buried. See exactly where you rank well and where you fall off. One scan tells you more about your local SEO than any dashboard metric.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Competitor geo-grid scanning for side-by-side comparison</h4><p>Overlay your heatmap against a competitor's and see precisely where they outrank you. Identifies geographic gaps to target with content and citations.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Historical trend tracking measures progress over time</h4><p>Stored scan history shows whether your local SEO investments are expanding your visibility radius week over week. Proof that your content strategy is working.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: tracking only — no content creation, no citation management</h4><p>Local Falcon tells you where you rank. It cannot help you rank higher. Pair it with theStacc for the content that moves the heatmap from red to green.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $39–$59/MO · MONTHLY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">BrightLocal — Best Full Local SEO Tracking Suite</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses and agencies that need geo-grid tracking plus citation audits, review monitoring, and GBP health scoring in one platform.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">BrightLocal wraps geo-grid Maps tracking inside a complete local SEO diagnostic platform. The geo-grid tracker shows your exact Maps position across a geographic grid — like Local Falcon, but bundled with citation audits across 80+ directories, review monitoring, and GBP completeness scoring. At $39–$59/month, it's the most complete picture of your local search health at this price point. The tradeoff: no content creation. BrightLocal diagnoses problems. You still need to fix them.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Geo-grid Maps tracking + citation audit + review monitoring in one platform</h4><p>More comprehensive than Local Falcon at a comparable price. See where you rank, what citations are wrong, and what reviews are coming in — all in one dashboard.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Citation tracker audits NAP data across 80+ directories</h4><p>One wrong phone number on a secondary directory confuses Google's trust signals. BrightLocal flags every inconsistency before it hurts your Maps ranking.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>GBP audit with optimization score and specific recommendations</h4><p>Missing categories, incomplete attributes, and description gaps flagged with actionable next steps. Not vague advice — a specific punch list.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: no GBP content creation — scheduling requires writing your own posts</h4><p>BrightLocal shows you what's wrong and where you rank. It does not create the content that fixes either. Pair with theStacc for automated GBP posts and blog articles.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · $19–$69/MO · MONTHLY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Localo — Best Budget GBP Optimizer for Maps Rankings</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For budget-conscious local businesses that want GBP audit, post templates, and local rank tracking in one affordable tool.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Localo is the most affordable GBP optimization tool that combines a profile audit, post templates, and local rank tracking in a single dashboard. At $19–$69/month, it covers GBP basics without stitching together multiple tools. The profile audit gives an optimization score and punch list. Post templates reduce writing time — but you still write every post. Rank tracking shows local keyword positions without the geographic depth of Local Falcon's heatmap.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Affordable entry point for GBP optimization at $19/month</h4><p>The cheapest paid tool that gives you both a GBP audit score and basic rank tracking. Good starting point before upgrading to BrightLocal.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>GBP audit score with actionable optimization checklist</h4><p>Simple interface accessible to business owners without SEO experience. The punch list tells you exactly what to fix to improve your profile completeness.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Post templates cut GBP writing time</h4><p>Template-based post creation for common GBP post types — offers, events, updates, news. Still requires customization, but faster than starting from scratch.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: templates mean you still do the writing — not true automation</h4><p>Localo helps you manage GBP more efficiently. For actual automation where the tool writes and publishes every post, theStacc's Local SEO module is the answer.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · FROM $25/MO · MONTHLY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Whitespark — Best Citation Building for Maps Rankings</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses that need manual citation building across top directories to support Maps ranking authority.</p>
        </div>
